1/8 cup extra virgin olive oil
1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice
coarse sea salt, to taste
ground black pepper, to taste
2 zucchinis
2 green onions
1/4 bunch fresh mint
1 cup cooked chicken
3 cups baby spinach
HOW TO PREPARE
1.	In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, sea salt, and pepper.
2.	Thinly slice the zucchini. Add the zucchini to the dressing and and toss to coat; allow to marinate while preparing the remaining ingredients.
3.	Mince the green onions and dice the mint. Shred the cooked chicken.
4.	Toss the shredded chicken with zucchini mixture. Add spinach, green onions, and mint. Season with sea salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
